📊 Modules in Bank Management System
1. User Management Module :
            Handles login, logout, and authentication
            Manages roles (admin, staff, customer)
2. Customer Management Module :
            Add, update, delete customer details
            Stores personal and account information
3. Account Management Module :
           Create new bank accounts
           Manage account types (savings, current)
           View account details
4. Transaction Module :
            Deposit money
            Withdraw money
            Transfer funds between accounts
5. Loan Management Module :
          Apply for loans
          Approve/reject loans
          Track loan details and repayments
6. Balance Inquiry Module :
         Check account balance
         View mini statements
7. Interest Calculation Module :
        Calculate interest for savings or loans
8. Report Generation Module :
      Generate account reports
      Transaction history reports
      Monthly/annual summaries
9. Security Module :
         Password protection
         Data encryption
        Fraud detection (basic level)
